Tattoo Fixers star Paisley Billings looks set to be heading into the I’m A Celebrity jungle. 
Celebs Go Dating viewers fell in love with her bubbly personality on the E4 show last series. 
And it seems it could happen again if she signs up for the ITV show - much like what happened with Queen of the Jungle Scarlett Moffatt last year. Tattoo Fixers star Paisley Billings for I Am A Celebrity Get Me Out Of Here (Photo: Channel 4/ITV) 
A source exclusively told Mirror Online: “Paisley has been doing amazingly well on E4 and is set to be the next Scarlett Moffatt if not bigger. Read More Paisley Billings has gone down a storm on Tattoo Fixers (Photo: Channel 4) She's the most famous of the four (Photo: Channel 4) 
“Paisley has a fantastic strong personality and she wasn't tipped to do well at the start of Tattoo Fixers but has done well as the only star on the show to do so many other shows. 
“Producers of the show I Am A Celebrity Get Me Out Of Here are talking and think if they put Paisley in the show she could go down a storm and possibly win it.” 
The source continued: “Paisley is getting to the stage that a lot of other channels and shows are wanting her. 
“Her hilarious personality has really gone down well with the public.” 
Kate Wright was another star to be recently rumoured for I’m A Celebrity, after reports she was quitting TOWIE for the jungle. Read More Stephanie Pratt stuns with shocking confession about her vagina on Celebs Go Dating She could be bigger than Scarlett Moffatt (Photo: Rex Features) 
The blonde beauty - who has recently been linked to former footballer Rio Ferdinand - was said to be hoping leaving the ITVBe show would boost her chances of being chosen for the jungle. 
A source had told Daily Star: "She knows casting for I’m A Celebrity begins in the spring and she’s knows if she gets picked she could leave TOWIE." 
But her rep has dismissed the claim as "rubbish". 
“Whilst Kate is a fan of I’m A Celebrity, she loves TOWIE and has a great relationship with the show so has no plans to leave right now,” the spokesperson told The Sun . Like us on Facebook
